6. Concrete example

User says:

“Look at this screenshot and tell me whether the architecture is right, then draft a better version.”

Pantheon flow:

Step 1: Normalize

Detect:
	•	input includes image
	•	likely goals:
	•	image understanding
	•	conceptual evaluation
	•	artifact generation

Step 2: Route
	•	VLM: read screenshot
	•	LLM: analyze concepts
	•	Retrieval: check known architecture taxonomy if needed
	•	Artifact generator: produce improved diagram/spec

Step 3: Translate

Convert all results into common objects:
	•	extracted labels
	•	confidence scores
	•	claims
	•	corrections

Step 4: Combine

Merged interpretation:
	•	“diagram is directionally right but mixes categories and paradigms”
	•	“recommended corrected structure is X”

Step 5: Constrain

Check:
	•	grounded?
	•	uncertain points labeled?
	•	no invented facts?

Step 6: Output

Return:
	•	explanation
	•	revised taxonomy
	•	maybe a diagram spec or image prompt

That is Pantheon functioning as nucleus.

