7. Math view

You asked earlier to map things to math. Here’s the clean version.

Let:
	•	x = input
	•	N(x) = normalized representation
	•	R = routing function
	•	M_i = specialist model i
	•	T = translation into shared schema
	•	C = combination / fusion
	•	K = constraint validator
	•	O = output renderer

Then:

z = N(x)

\{M_i\} = R(z)

y_i = M_i(z)

u_i = T(y_i)

u^* = C(u_1, u_2, ..., u_n)

v = K(u^*)

\text{Output} = O(v)

So Pantheon is not a single model:
P(x) = O(K(C(T(M_{R(N(x))}(N(x)))))))

Messy notation, but the idea is clear:
Pantheon is the composition law.

