9. Biggest engineering risks

A. Shared schema too vague

If the interlingua is sloppy, the whole thing turns to mush.

B. Over-routing

If Pantheon calls everything all the time, it becomes expensive and slow.

C. False synthesis

Combining multiple outputs can produce elegant nonsense unless checked.

D. Memory pollution

Bad summaries contaminate future steps.

E. Mythic naming without hard boundaries

The names are good for design intuition, but each module needs strict I/O contracts.

