10. Hard design rule

Every daemon/module needs:
	•	input type
	•	output type
	•	allowed actions
	•	confidence semantics
	•	failure mode
	•	audit log

Example:

Hound
	•	Input: claim set, evidence set
	•	Output: anomaly report
	•	Allowed actions: flag contradiction, lower confidence, request verification
	•	Failure mode: overflagging ambiguous novelty

That’s how you keep it real.

